title: Boy fights for life after Sydney shark attack | 7NEWS
description: A 12-year-old boy, Nico Antic, remains in critical condition at Sydney Children's Hospital after suffering severe injuries to both legs in a bull shark attack at Jump Rock, Vaucluse, in Sydney Harbour. His friends pulled him from murky water and water police provided crucial first aid before he was rushed to hospital. Less than 24 hours later, a suspected bull shark also took a large bite from an 11-year-old's surfboard at Dee Why Beach, though the child was uninjured. Authorities have closed more than 20 swimming spots around the harbour and are urging swimmers to avoid murky water conditions following heavy rain. title: Blood test detects pancreatic cancer early | 7NEWS
description: A new blood test can detect pancreatic cancer before symptoms appear, using technology similar to pregnancy tests to identify cancer DNA in the bloodstream. The test analyses DNA from dying cells to find cancer in people who appear healthy. Professor Steve Robson, a specialist obstetrician, became the first Australian to take the test, which currently costs nearly $1,500 and is not covered by Medicare.
